<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Services | Fariborz Aref Web Studio</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <meta name="description" content="Services for academic web design, journal sites, and research institutes." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <header class="site-header">
    <div class="shell header-inner">
      <div class="brand">
        <span class="brand-mark">FA</span>
        <div class="brand-meta">
          <span class="brand-name">Fariborz Aref Web Studio</span>
          <span class="brand-tagline">Academic web design and consulting</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <button class="nav-toggle" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
      </button>

      <nav class="nav">
        <a href="index.html">Home</a>
        <a href="services.html" class="active">Services</a>
        <a href="work.html">Work</a>
        <a href="about.html">About</a>
        <a href="contact.html">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="shell">
        <h1>Services</h1>
        <p>
          Focused, practical web services built for academics, journals, and research projects.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="shell grid-2">
        <div>
          <h2>Academic sites</h2>
          <p>
            Personal websites for faculty, postdocs, and researchers who need a single place
            to present their work. These sites are simple to update and suitable for grant
            and job applications.
          </p>
          <ul class="bullet-list">
            <li>Home page with clear introduction</li>
            <li>Publications with basic citation layout</li>
            <li>Teaching, supervision, and service sections</li>
            <li>Optional blog or notes area</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Journal and series sites</h2>
          <p>
            Structured sites for journals and series that keep calls, author guidelines, and
            issue information in a single clean layout.
          </p>
          <ul class="bullet-list">
            <li>Calls for papers pages</li>
            <li>Submission guidelines and templates</li>
            <li>Editorial board profiles</li>
            <li>Issue or volume archive sections</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-alt">
      <div class="shell grid-2">
        <div>
          <h2>Research institute sites</h2>
          <p>
            Sites for labs, centers, and institutes that work with partners, grants,
            and community projects. The focus is on clarity, not slogans.
          </p>
          <ul class="bullet-list">
            <li>Services and methods explained in simple language</li>
            <li>Project and partner highlights</li>
            <li>Team or affiliate profiles if needed</li>
            <li>Clear path to request a consultation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Support and consulting</h2>
          <p>
            For teams that already have a site but need structure, content editing,
            or design clean up without rebuilding everything from zero.
          </p>
          <ul class="bullet-list">
            <li>Menu and navigation review</li>
            <li>Section layout and content audit</li>
            <li>Home page clarity and messaging</li>
            <li>Technical check for static sites on GitHub Pages</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2>How projects are scoped</h2>
          <p>
            Every project begins with a brief, timeline, and clear cost. No hidden parts.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Short discovery</h3>
            <p>
              You share goals, existing materials, and constraints. One focused call or email
              exchange is enough for a first scope.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Simple proposal</h3>
            <p>
              You receive a written outline with pages, features, estimated time, and a clear
              price range before anything starts.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Delivery and handoff</h3>
            <p>
              When the site is complete, you receive the full codebase on GitHub plus basic
              instructions for maintenance or small edits.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <p>To discuss a specific project, send a short description of what you need.</p>
          <a href="contact.html" class="btn primary">Go to contact page</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <div class="shell footer-inner">
      <div class="footer-brand">
        <span class="brand-mark small">FA</span>
        <span>Fariborz Aref Web Studio</span>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-meta">
        Academic and research web design · Houston, Texas · © 2025
      </div>
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="index.html">Home</a>
        <a href="services.html">Services</a>
        <a href="work.html">Work</a>
        <a href="about.html">About</a>
        <a href="contact.html">Contact</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script src="assets/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
